name: February 1, 2003, Prior to the Space Shuttle Columbia Crash
description:
The Space Shuttle Columbia disaster was a fatal incident in the United States space program that occurred on February 1, 2003, when the Space Shuttle Columbia disintegrated as it reentered the atmosphere, killing all seven crew members. 
Date: February 1, 2003
Number of deaths: 7
Cause: Wing damage from debris during launch
Location: Texas, Louisiana
